# POLIS — Editing Conventions

## Code style

- Everything is global in one `<script>`. Names are intentionally **terse**
  (`S` = state, `G` = grid, `c` = cell, `cx` = canvas ctx). Match it.
- Comments explain **why / balance intent**, not what. Preserve them; they
  encode hard-won tuning. Do not add narration comments.
- Plain ES (no TypeScript, no modules, no JSX). Don't introduce a build step,
  bundler, or npm dependency — the single-file, zero-dependency nature is a
  core feature (it must run by just opening the file).

## After changing the map or cell data, refresh derived state

The simulation caches a lot. When you mutate `map`, cell types, or networks:

```js
recomputeNets();     // power + water flood-fill (only if connectivity changed)
recomputeFields();   // pollution / crime / land value / coverage
dirty = true;        // force the next frame to redraw (renderer is decoupled)
```

Forgetting `dirty = true` is the usual cause of "my change doesn't show up":
the frame governor skips redraws when idle.

## Adding a new building / tile type — checklist

Tile types are serialized **by array index**, so order is load-bearing:

- [ ] Append the id to **`TYPE_IDS`** (~10738) — **never reorder or remove**
      existing entries, or every saved city breaks.
- [ ] Add a display name in `NAMES` (~9104).
- [ ] Register it in the relevant trait tables so systems pick it up:
      `ZONE`/`SVC`/`ROADTYPE`/`WALKTYPE`/`CONDUCT`, plus `UPKEEP`, and
      `CAP`/`PLANT`/`WSRC`/`LEIS`/`FOOT` as applicable.
- [ ] Add it to the `TOOLS` catalog (~963) with cost `c`, icon, group.
- [ ] Give it a draw path in `render()` / a `draw*` function.
- [ ] Handle placement in `place()` (~2211) if it needs special rules.

## Save format

`makeSave()` (~10798) / `loadSave()` (~10803) encode the city as
`TLV5.<base64(JSON)>`: per-cell `[typeIndex, lv, dev, overlayBitmask]` plus `S`
fields (the current `TLV5` also carries player terrain heights `eh`). If you
change the cell payload shape, **bump the version prefix** (`TLV5`→`TLV6`) and
keep `loadSave` able to read older codes — it already branches by version on
stride/bitmask (`TLV2` stride 3, `TLV3` enum 4th value, `TLV4`/`TLV5` overlay
bitmask). Persistent slots go through `store` (artifact API → localStorage
fallback); autosave fires monthly.

## Balance tuning

Gameplay numbers live in **named tables**, not scattered literals — tune there:
`UPKEEP`, `CAP`, `PLANT`, `WSRC`, `LEIS`, `ROAD_CAP`, `DIFF`, `LOAN_OFFERS`,
and the growth thresholds inside `simTick()`. Prefer adjusting a table constant
over editing per-tile logic.

## Testing changes

There is a headless **Playwright** suite in `tests/` (`cd tests && npm ci &&
npm test`; CI runs it on every push/PR via `.github/workflows/test.yml`). It
loads the real `index.html` via `file://` so every global exists, and asserts
**invariants** — save round-trips, the budget accounting identity, growth
gating, network flood-fill, loan amortization — instead of golden numbers, so
honest balance tuning stays green. Determinism leans on the test-only RNG seam
`__seedRng`/`__unseedRng` (~937); in normal play the RNG is `Math.random`.
Add/extend a `*.spec.js` when you touch the sim, and keep new assertions
invariant-based. If you change `TYPE_IDS` or the save payload, the round-trip
specs are the safety net — run them.

Also verify in-browser: open `index.html` (or `python3 -m http.server`), load a
demo with `loadDemo(EXAMPLE_CITY)`, and watch the stats charts modal. The game
is **mobile-first** (pointer events, pinch-zoom, DPR-aware canvas) —
sanity-check touch interactions when touching input or layout.
